commText: Dhawan and Bairstow are at the crease. Dhawan is on strike. Siraj will open the attack

Siraj to Dhawan, FOUR, swing, fumble and four. Full and hint of swing back into the left hander, Dhawan drives crisply to the right of mid-off, Maxwell moves across and dives, gets a hand and allows it to escape past him. He's livid..
Anuj is keeping. One slip in place
Siraj to Dhawan, no run, good length ball on off, Dhawan stays behind the line and defends to the off-side
Siraj to Dhawan, 2 runs, swinging into the pads and Dhawan manages to pierce the flick past mid-wicket, DK chases from square leg and keeps it to a brace
There's a strong leg-side field - square leg, mid-wicket, mid-on and fine leg
Siraj to Dhawan, 1 run, once more strays onto the pads and Dhawan clips it backward of square leg, just a single
Bairstow vs Siraj in the IPL: Runs: 46 Balls: 20 Dismissals: 0 SR: 230 4s/6s: 5/4
Siraj to Bairstow, no run, I0$ full pitcher around off, Bairstow pushes it to mid-off
Siraj to Bairstow, no run, good length ball close to off, Bairstow prods forward and defends to the off-side
Yash Dayal, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Yash Dayal to Dhawan, no run, I0$ back of a length delivery in the channel, Dhawan makes a late decision to shoulder arms
Yash Dayal to Dhawan, no run, I0$ outswinger outside off, Dhawan lifts his bat and lets it go
Yash Dayal to Dhawan, no run, nice shape once again away from the left hander, Dhawan hides his bat and lets it pass
Yash Dayal to Dhawan, no run, now the inswinger, Dhawan brings his bat down and knocks it to cover. Dayal thought he was through Dhawan's defences
Slip in place. Third man inside the ring
Yash Dayal to Dhawan, 1 run, shimmies down the wicket and is met by a short of length delivery, drops it with soft hands to the off-side and Bairstow responds to the call of a quick single
Yash Dayal to Bairstow, leg byes, 1 run, nip-backer from short of length as Bairstow walks down, he's beaten on the inside edge and struck on the thigh pad, the ball rolls to the vacant point region

Siraj to Bairstow, FOUR, proper miscue but Bairstow is not complaining. Good length ball and with a hint of inward shape, Bairstow wanted to loft down town but gets it off the inner half and the ball flies over wide mid-on
Siraj to Bairstow, FOUR, that's right off the middle. On a length and outside off, Bairstow had the width and he cracks it square of the wicket
Siraj to Bairstow, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Siraj to Bairstow, out Caught by Kohli!! Siraj has the last say. Early breakthrough for RCB and the crowd are pumped. Siraj pulled his length back after pitching a couple up, this was short of length and hurried onto Bairstow, he goes for the pull and gets it high on the bat, the ball goes straight up towards cover, Kohli (from cover) and Maxwell (from mid-off) converge, the latter leaves it for the former. Bairstow c Kohli b Siraj 8(6) [4s-2]
Bairstow vs RCB: 114(56), Hyderabad, 2019 61(43), Dubai, 2020 12(13), Chennai, 2021 66(29), Brabourne, 2022 8(6), Bengaluru, 2024
Prabhsimran Singh, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Siraj to Prabhsimran, no run, short of length on off, Prabhsimran gets on top of the bounce and defends to the off-side

Siraj to Prabhsimran, FOUR, just a push and the ball races away. Siraj cannot believe it. Scrambled seam delivery around off, Prabhsimran presents the full face of the bat and eases it down the wicket. Faf gets across from mid-on and dives but the timing is too good
Siraj to Prabhsimran, no run, back of a length around off, Prabhsimran stays leg-side and knocks it to the off-side
Yash Dayal to Dhawan, no run, comes down the track and sees the ball swing away, shoulders arms
Yash Dayal to Dhawan, 1 run, once more advances and is met by a short of length delivery, steers it to deep backward point
Yash Dayal to Prabhsimran, no run, I0$ short of length angled across, Prabhsimran rides the bounce and pats it to point
India fielders with most catches in Men’s T20 cricket 173 - Virat Kohli 172 - Suresh Raina 167 - Rohit Sharma 146 - Manish Pandey 136 - Suryakumar Yadav
Still a slip in place for Dayal
Yash Dayal to Prabhsimran, 1 run, good length ball angled across, Prabhsimran shuffles and dabs it to third man
Yash Dayal to Dhawan, 1 run, full pitcher around off, Dhawan eases it to mid-off and crosses over comfortably
Yash Dayal to Prabhsimran, no run, back of a length outside off, Prabhsimran punches towards cover and Kohli is quick to pounce on it
Alzarri Joseph, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Alzarri Joseph to Dhawan, no run, I0$ good length ball and not quite on the driving arc, Dhawan mistimes it towards mid-off
Alzarri bowling from round the wicket. He too has a slip

Alzarri Joseph to Dhawan, FOUR, I0$ half volley and Dhawan is not missing out this time, he opens the bat face and intentionally goes aerial with his drive, clears the infield and picks up a much needed boundary
Alzarri Joseph to Dhawan, no run, on a length and close to off, Dhawan defends to the cover region
Alzarri Joseph to Dhawan, no run, I0$ back of a length in the channel, Dhawan punches it firmly to cover and picks out Kohli

Alzarri Joseph to Dhawan, FOUR, mid-off is quite wide and Maxi can't stop this even with the drive. I0$ full pitcher and Dhawan eases the drive to the left of mid-off. The timing was good enough to take it past Maxi
Alzarri Joseph to Dhawan, 2 runs, short of length delivery, Dhawan rides the bounce and steers it past short third. Dayal gets around from deep backward point and makes a fine stop, saved a couple

Yash Dayal to Prabhsimran, no run, I0$ fuller and slanted outside off, Prabhsimran looks to launch it out of the ground and is beaten by the angle. He's feeling the pressure and this is the last over in the powerplay

Yash Dayal to Prabhsimran, FOUR, miscue and the ball teases Maxi all the way to the rope. Good length ball and Prabhsimran slices the drive over extra cover. Not off the middle and hence the ball didn't race away
Yash Dayal to Prabhsimran, 1 run, walks down and nudges it towards mid-wicket, Prabhsimran rushes to the other end and beats the direct hit

Yash Dayal to Dhawan, no run, that's a peach. He's bowled really well without anything to show. Back of a length and in the channel, Dhawan is squared up as the ball straightens and goes past the outside edge
Yash Dayal to Dhawan, no run, spots Dhawan charge down and cramps him for room, the ball hits him on the pad and drops to the off-side
Mohammed Siraj in the PP at Chinnaswamy since 2023 Overs: 18 Runs conceded: 85 Wickets: 7 Avg: 12.14 ER: 4.72 Dots: 72 (66.67%)
Yash Dayal to Dhawan, 1 run, I0$ back of a length close to off, Dhawan shuffles and pats it square of the wicket

Powerplay summary -- RCB pacers get the new ball to swing -- Siraj gets rid of Bairstow for 8 -- Dayal bowls with good accuracy to keep it tight -- Dhawan plays some lovely shots to get going -- Joseph's first over goes for 10
Cameron Green, right-arm medium, comes into the attack
Green to Dhawan, no run, I0$ back of a length on off, Dhawan knocks it firmly to cover
Green to Dhawan, wide, attempted yorker gone wrong, sprays it outside off and Dhawan ignores
Green to Dhawan, 1 run, fuller and outside off, Dhawan crunches the drive square and Siraj tidies up in the deep
Green to Prabhsimran, no run, I0$ hits the three quarter length and gets that extra bounce, Prabhsimran swings through the line and is beaten on the outside edge

Green to Prabhsimran, SIX, that should calm him down. He was itching to have a go and finally connects with one. Full delivery on off, Prabhsimran shuffles across and whips it into the second tier at deep square leg
Green to Prabhsimran, 1 run, on a length and outside off, Prabhsimran angles it wide of backward point and rotates strike
Green to Dhawan, 1 run, angled in from round the wicket, Dhawan goes hard on the drive and drags it off the inner half through mid-wicket
Mayank Dagar, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Mayank Dagar to Dhawan, 1 run, drifted across from round the wicket, Dhawan knocks it in front of long-on
Mayank Dagar to Prabhsimran, 1 run, comes down the track and does not quite get hold of the loft, mistimed to long-on
Mayank Dagar to Dhawan, 1 run, flatter and sliding across, Dhawan sweeps and drags it off the inside edge towards mid-wicket
Mayank Dagar to Prabhsimran, 1 run, short and drifting in, Prabhsimran sits down and pulls to long leg
Mayank Dagar to Dhawan, SIX, that was smartly bowled but Dhawan was up for it. Dagar saw Dhawan shimmy down and fired it outside off, but Dhawan managed to reach it and loft it over long-on
Mayank Dagar to Dhawan, 1 run, full, fast and outside off, Dhawan drives square of the wicket and retains strike

Timeout! It has been a steady start from Punjab Kings. They're getting a hang of the conditions and setting themselves up for the second half of the innings. RCB won't mind this scoring rate but would do well with 1-2 wickets in the next couple of overs.
Glenn Maxwell, right-arm off break, comes into the attack
Maxwell to Dhawan, FOUR, short and outside off, Dhawan cuts it square and beats Siraj in the deep. Good start after the break..
Maxwell to Dhawan, 1 run, tossed up on off, Dhawan works it against the spin to long-on
Over the wicket to Prabhsimran
Maxwell to Prabhsimran, no run, flatter and fraction short, Prabhsimran is hurried on the pull and he misses, struck high on the pad

Maxwell to Prabhsimran, SIX, just over the rope. This was a heave and Prabhsimran managed to get it over the rope. Fired full at the stumps, Prabhsimran goes across the line and clears deep backward square
Maxwell to Prabhsimran, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Maxwell to Prabhsimran, out Caught by Anuj Rawat!! The partnership has been broken. Maxwell shortens the length and extracts more bounce, Prabhsimran looks to pull but the bounce deceives him, the top-edge goes straight up and Anuj Rawat moves to his left to complete a simple catch. Prabhsimran c Anuj Rawat b Maxwell 25(17) [4s-2 6s-2]
Liam Livingstone, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Maxwell to Livingstone, no run, turn and bounce for Maxwell. Short of length and spins, Livingstone shuffles across and is beaten on the inside edge, the ball strikes him on the back thigh
Mayank Dagar to Dhawan, 1 run, flatter and drifted across, Dhawan nudges it to deep square leg
Mayank Dagar to Livingstone, no run, flighted outside off, Livingstone angles it to backward point
Stumping check sent upstairs. Anuj Rawat and RCB are not interested. Nothing on UltraEdge for a caught behind check. The back leg is grounded behind the crease. Not Out..

Mayank Dagar to Livingstone, no run, this was nicely bowled. Tosses it up outside off and draws Livingstone forward, the ball spins away to beat the outside edge and Anuj Rawat is quick to light up the stumps
Mayank Dagar to Livingstone, 1 run, shorter and quicker, Livingstone slaps it straight to sweeper cover
Mayank Dagar to Dhawan, no run, comes down the track and gets a low full toss, jams it to extra cover

Mayank Dagar to Dhawan, FOUR, in the air and just wide. What is Dayal doing at backward point? Short and sliding across, Dhawan goes for the cut but is not in control of the shot and slices it to the left of Dayal. He puts the dive but is well away from his reach
Maxwell to Livingstone, 1 run, fired full around off, Livingstone works it to long-on
Round the wicket to Dhawan
Maxwell to Dhawan, 1 run, short of length on middle, Dhawan tucks it to square leg
Maxwell to Livingstone, FOUR, what placement! Livingstone shuffles across and is quick to pick the shortish length, pulls it in front of square and bisects deep mid-wicket and long-on perfectly
Maxwell to Livingstone, 2 runs, comes down the track and gets too close to the pitch, drills it to long-on and Alzarri makes a half stop, easy two
Maxwell to Livingstone, no run, short and spinning in, Livingstone stays back and knocks it to cover

Maxwell to Livingstone, SIX, that was a miscue. Anuj Rawat even shouted catch it but Kohli was well in from the boundary rope. Would he have had a chance had he stayed right on the edge? Livingstone mistimes the slog sweep and gets away with it as the ball lands just beyond the deep mid-wicket fence
Alzarri Joseph [1.0-0-10-0] is back into the attack
Alzarri Joseph to Dhawan, 1 run, tight single. Back of a length on off, Dhawan angles it to backward point and Livingstone is off, Dagar with a shy at the striker's end and the throw is not on target
Alzarri Joseph to Livingstone, 2 runs, nails the yorker perfectly, Livingstone digs it into the vast open spaces on the leg-side and races back
Alzarri Joseph to Livingstone, no run, I0$ delivery pounded into hard length area, Livingstone swings across the line and the ball sneaks under his bat
Alzarri Joseph to Livingstone, wide, sprays the short ball outside off, Livingstone ignores it and the umpire signals a wide
Alzarri Joseph to Livingstone, 1 run, slower short ball and Livingstone delays his pull, plays it along the ground to deep mid-wicket
Alzarri Joseph to Dhawan, 1 run, I0$ short and at the body, Dhawan is rushed on the pull and gloves it backward of square leg
Alzarri Joseph to Livingstone, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Alzarri Joseph to Livingstone, out Caught by Anuj Rawat!! First wicket for Alzarri as RCB bowler. Once again it is that hard length which works for him. But Livingstone would be disappointed as this was there to be put away. Banged into the wicket outside off, Livingstone throws his bat on the slash and the top-edge flies to Anuj Rawat, he leaps up and hangs on safely. Livingstone c Anuj Rawat b Alzarri Joseph 17(13) [4s-1 6s-1]
Sam Curran, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Maxwell to Dhawan, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Maxwell to Dhawan, out Caught by Kohli!! Back to back wickets. The set batter is gone. Maxwell is pumped. Kohli is calm. The fans are shouting "RCB, RCB, RCB". Dhawan comes down the track and looks to loft, but the ball spins away a tad and catches the outer half, sliced to long-off and Kohli takes a simple catch. Two new batters in the middle and right now it is advantage RCB. Dhawan c Kohli b Maxwell 45(37) [4s-5 6s-1]
Jitesh Sharma, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Maxwell to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, flighted around off, Jitesh works it to long-on
Maxwell to Sam Curran, 1 run, flatter and sliding in, Curran brings his bat down and tucks it to mid-wicket
Maxwell to Jitesh Sharma, no run, quicker and at the stumps, Jitesh turns it gently to mid-wicket
Dhawan vs Maxwell in T20s Runs: 107 Balls: 66 Dismissals: 4 Avg: 26.75 SR: 162.12
Maxwell to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, tossed up outside off, Jitesh drives inside out wide of long-off and Green keeps it to a single
Maxwell to Sam Curran, 1 run, drifting in with the angle, Curran knocks it to long-on and retains strike
Cameron Green [1.0-0-10-0] is back into the attack
Green to Sam Curran, 1 run, 141.9kph, round the wicket, full on the pads, flicked to fine leg
Over the wicket to Jitesh Sharma
Green to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, 130kph, full outside off, driven to deep point off the front foot
Green to Sam Curran, 2 runs, short of length, tucked to the left of mid-on where Siraj dives and fails to stop it. Easy two as deep midwicket mops it up
Green to Sam Curran, FOUR, 136.8kph, head-high bouncer and Sam Curran goes after it with a pull shot. Decent contact despite taking his eyes off the ball. Over square leg for a one-bounce four
Green to Sam Curran, 1 run, 132.2kph, short ball, a hopping Curran turns it towards midwicket
Green to Jitesh Sharma, no run, 126.5kph, fuller length ball angled in, knocked back to the bowler

Highlights (Overs 7-14) -- 71/3 -- PBKS on the back foot as wickets tumble -- Maxwell strikes in his first over to get rid of Prabhsimran (8.5) -- Joseph removes Livingstone for 17 (11.6) -- Dhawan falls to Maxwell for 45 (12.1)
Mayank Dagar [2.0-0-17-0] is back into the attack
Mayank Dagar to Sam Curran, 2 runs, 93.3kph, round the wicket, away-dart outside off, cut hard through point. Kohli runs to his right and makes a diving stop to save a couple of runs
Mayank Dagar to Sam Curran, 1 run, 91.2kph, shorter in length, width on offer again and Curran cuts to Kohli's left for a single
Mayank Dagar to Jitesh Sharma, no run, 89.9kph, short of a good length that holds onto the pitch a bit, a backing away Jitesh chops it to cover off the under-edge
Mayank Dagar to Jitesh Sharma, SIX, wow! 94kph, Jitesh Sharma dances down the track and lofts it downtown. With his back leg off the ground he thumps it stylishly. Comes right off the meat of the bat
Mayank Dagar to Jitesh Sharma, SIX, 92.3kph, in-dart on leg from a short of length, Jitesh Sharma stays back on this occasion to hammer the pull over deep square leg. Back-to-back sixes!
Mayank Dagar to Jitesh Sharma, 2 runs, moves leg-side and sweetly drives to the left of long-off for a couple more. 17 runs off the over!
Mohammed Siraj [2.0-0-19-1] is back into the attack
Siraj to Sam Curran, 1 run, 137.2kph, short of length ball from over the wicket, slapped to the left of extra cover who makes a diving stop
Siraj to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, 133.7kph, hits the deck hard on a back of a length, Jitesh skips down the track to slash it away to deep cover

Siraj to Sam Curran, byes, 1 run, 125.6kph, slower ball bouncer marginally outside off, Sam Curran lets it be. Falls short of the keeper and the ball deflects away off the keeper's pads. Siraj isn't happy with that effort from Rawat
Siraj to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, 141.4kph, fuller length ball, stylishly flicked to deep midwicket for a single
Siraj to Sam Curran, no run, 134.7kph, second bouncer of the over. Sam Curran shapes to pull and misses as the ball goes over the blade. Siraj wears a smile...

Siraj to Sam Curran, no run, 139.8kph, very full almost in the blockhole, drilled back at the bowler who stops it in his followthrough. Siraj stares at Curran and the two players exchange a few words as well. Excellent over from Siraj!
Timeout! RCB have done a good job with the ball so far. Can they finish it well? This is the key partnership for Punjab. Jitesh Sharma has looked in good touch and they need a strong finish here
Alzarri Joseph [2.0-0-16-1] is back into the attack
Alzarri Joseph to Jitesh Sharma, no run, 142.1kph, length ball around off, Jitesh Sharma drives straight to extra cover

Alzarri Joseph to Jitesh Sharma, FOUR, 121.9kph, slower ball on a fullish length, Jitesh Sharma swings hard in an attempt to go over midwicket, gets a thick inside edge that eludes the leg-stump and dribbles away to fine leg for four. Streaky but Punjab won't mind
Alzarri Joseph to Jitesh Sharma, no run, 143.8kph, hard length, Jitesh sees the width and flashes his bat, doesn't connect as the ball bounces over his blade
Alzarri Joseph to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, 140.7kph, very full, wristily flicked to the right of long-on who moves across and takes it on the bounce
Alzarri Joseph to Sam Curran, 1 run, 144.4kph, back of a length ball, a hopping Curran tucks it to deep square leg
Alzarri Joseph to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, 148.8kph, shortish on the ribs, Jitesh swivels and pulls towards long leg. Another good over for RCB
Three overs remain. Siraj and Joseph will certainly bowl one each. The other one to be bowled by Yash...
Yash Dayal [3.0-0-10-0] is back into the attack
Yash Dayal to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, 140.1kph, low full toss, drilled to the left of mid-off where Faf makes a diving stop. Jitesh is livid as he failed to find the gap
Yash Dayal to Sam Curran, wide, 139.5kph, goes for the wide yorker and ends up bowling this outside the tramline, left alone by the batter for it to be wided
Yash Dayal to Sam Curran, FOUR, 135.4kph, full toss below the waist and Sam Curran clears his front leg to smash it straight of mid-off. Poor delivery and punished!
Yash Dayal to Sam Curran, no run, nails the yorker outside off, Curran throws his bat at it but doesn't make contact
Yash Dayal to Sam Curran, wide, 103kph, slower ball bouncer, too short outside off, a hopping Curran lets it go. Faf has a word with his bowler
Yash Dayal to Sam Curran, FOUR, 140.8kph, full toss angled in, Curran shuffles across and swings it over square leg. No one is stopping that. The boundary brings up the fifty partnership!
Yash Dayal to Sam Curran, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Yash Dayal to Sam Curran, out Caught by Anuj Rawat!! Excellent grab by Anuj Rawat! 141.7kph, well-directed bouncer, Curran looks to hook it away but it hurried by this delivery. Only manages to get a glove on it and Rawat times his jump perfectly to pouch it with his right hand. Sam Curran c Anuj Rawat b Yash Dayal 23(17) [4s-3]
Shashank Singh, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Yash Dayal to Shashank Singh, 2 runs, 135.4kph, full on the stumps, worked into the midwicket pocket and the batters come back for the second. The throw comes to the bowler's end and fortunately for Jitesh Sharma, there's no direct-hit. He was well short of his ground. Suyash got to the ball swiftly and released it quickly despite being off-balance. 13 runs and a wicket off Yash Dayal's final over and he finishes with 1/23
Mohammed Siraj [3.0-0-22-1] is back into the attack

Siraj to Jitesh Sharma, no run, 138.7kph, wide yorker, Jitesh Sharma shoulders arms. PBKS have reviewed it for a wide. "Some of the ball is within the guidline," says the TV umpire and Punjab lose a review
Siraj to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, full toss, Jitesh Sharma swings hard and mishits, falls well short of the forward-running long-on fielder
Siraj to Shashank Singh, 1 run, short ball, Shashank Singh walks across to pull and the ball hits him high on the bat. A single as the ball rolls towards mid-on
Siraj to Jitesh Sharma, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Siraj to Jitesh Sharma, out Caught by Anuj Rawat!! In the air, Anuj Rawat calls for it, moves towards point and completes the catch. 130.3kph, banged in short outside off, Jitesh Sharma loses his shape as he looks to slap it through the off-side. Splices it up in the air and Anuj Rawat doesn't err. Oh, the TV umpire has been called to check if it has hit the spider cam wire. Bruce Oxenford is convinced that it hasn't made contact with the cable. Big blow for Punjab! Jitesh Sharma c Anuj Rawat b Siraj 27(20) [4s-1 6s-2]
Harpreet Brar, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Siraj to Harpreet Brar, 2 runs, full on leg, flicked through midwicket for a couple of runs

Siraj to Harpreet Brar, no run, 140.5kph, goes for the yorker, ends up bowling a low full toss outside off. Harpreet Brar tries to cheekily run it down to third man but doesn't connect. Excellent stuff from Siraj who finishes with 2/26!
Alzarri Joseph [3.0-0-23-1] is back into the attack
Alzarri Joseph to Shashank Singh, SIX, much-needed for Punjab! 140.3kph, overpitched on middle and leg, Shashank walks across, crouches a bit and flicks it handsomely over deep backward square leg

Alzarri Joseph to Shashank Singh, no run, Joseph pulls his length back but bowls it outside off, Shashank shuffles and slashes. Wided and RCB review it. Well outside the tramline but even the batter has moved a long way. "The movement of the batter across is more than the ball is outside the line of wide guideline," says the TV umpire. That looked wide to the naked eye but it's a successful review
Alzarri Joseph to Shashank Singh, SIX, slow and short, Shashank walks across and pummels it over deep midwicket. Waited for it and sent it into the stands
Alzarri Joseph to Shashank Singh, FOUR, short and wide of off, Shashank throws his bat at it, gets a fat edge that flies over short third man. Punjab cross 170!
Alzarri Joseph to Shashank Singh, 1 run, 126.9kph, length outside off, Shashank throws the kitchen sink and slices it over point

Alzarri Joseph to Harpreet Brar, 2 wides, 142.5kph, full ball down leg, Brar shuffles and misses the flick and the batters steal a single as well. RCB review again! "Ball is clearly down leg," says Oxenford and the onfield call stays
Alzarri Joseph to Shashank Singh, 1 run, slower ball on a length, heaved down to long-on. Harpreet Brar wants the second gets sent back

21:12 Local Time, 15:42 GMT, 21:12 IST: 20 runs off the last over, a good little cameo from Shashank Singh and Punjab finish on 176 - probably a below-par score. Siraj provided the early breakthrough by removing Bairstow after conceding back-to-back boundaries. Yash Dayal swung the new ball and kept it tight. Prabhsimran and Dhawan stitched a fifty partnership at a decent rate before Maxwell removed the former. Livingstone came in at four and struck a couple of boundaries off Maxwell's bowling. Joseph bowled the hard length to nip out the English power-hitter and Dhawan fell the very next ball to become Maxi's second victim. At 98/4 in the 13th over, Punjab had two new batters out in the middle and RCB bowled well despite the Curran-Jitesh duo forging a half-ton partnership. Siraj bowled a superb penultimate over but Alzarri leaked 20 runs off the final over. RCB have a power-packed batting line-up and they can also bring in an additional batter as the impact sub. So, they'll fancy their chances to chase this down. How will the visitors fare with the ball? Join us in a bit to find out...

Sam Curran: It is probably slightly under par. But it (the surface) is not a belter, good finish by the boys and a few early wickets can get us back. They bowled really with the new ball and there was some help for the spinners. We are going out there with a plan and make 176 enough.
RCB bowling today: \nSiraj and Dayal: 3/49 from 8 overs (ER: 6.125) \nOthers: 3/125 from 12 overs (ER: 10.42)
Shashank Singh batting in the 20th over in the IPL SRH vs GT, Mumbai WS, 2022: 6, 6, 6 off Lockie Ferguson Today: 6, 0, 6, 4, 1, 1 off Alzarri Joseph Total: 36 off 9, SR: 400
- Anuj Rawat becomes the first wicketkeeper to bag four dismissals in an innings for RCB.
Stats by Roshan Gede
Welcome back. The players make their way out to the middle. Impact sub: Arshdeep Singh comes in for Prabhsimran. Sam Curran has the new ball in his hand. A slip in position. Here we go...
